[
    {
        "content": "<p>Is there a theorem in Mathlib saying that the Lebesgue measure of a measurable subset of  <code>ℝ</code> is invariant under translation?  Somehow I can find similar results about scaling, but not translation.</p>",
        "id": 488762495,
        "sender_full_name": "Ching-Tsun Chou",
        "timestamp": 1734063860
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The keyword should be \"Haar measure\"</p>",
        "id": 488763062,
        "sender_full_name": "Bjørn Kjos-Hanssen",
        "timestamp": 1734064197
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=IsHaarMeasure#doc\">docs#IsHaarMeasure</a> is defined in the second half of <code>MeasureTheory.Group.Measure</code>; further up in the same file are results on general left- and right-invariant measures, which are probably what you are looking for. I haven't looked too closely, but for example <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=MeasureTheory.map_add_left_eq_self#doc\">docs#MeasureTheory.map_add_left_eq_self</a> seems relevant.</p>",
        "id": 488763684,
        "sender_full_name": "Ben Eltschig",
        "timestamp": 1734064638
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks!  I wouldn't have found it myself.</p>",
        "id": 488764939,
        "sender_full_name": "Ching-Tsun Chou",
        "timestamp": 1734065482
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><del>I was able to prove the result I want:</del></p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">volume</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">image</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↦</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">volume</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"bp\">←</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">map_add_left_eq_self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">volume</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p><del>But I have to say I do not understand the proof at all.  Even weirder, <code>map_add_right_eq_self</code> also works:</del></p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">volume</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">image</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↦</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">volume</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"bp\">←</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">map_add_right_eq_self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">volume</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Well, using <code>simp?</code>, I found that neither theorems are actually needed:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">volume</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">image</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↦</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">volume</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">only</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">image_add_right</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">measure_preimage_add_right</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 488920639,
        "sender_full_name": "Ching-Tsun Chou",
        "timestamp": 1734123922
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Now I have another question: which result in Mathlib will allow me to prove the following?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MeasurableSet</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MeasurableSet</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">image</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↦</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 488920914,
        "sender_full_name": "Ching-Tsun Chou",
        "timestamp": 1734124014
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That last one is</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MeasurableSet</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MeasurableSet</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">((</span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↦</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">''</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">MeasurableEquiv</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">addRight</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">measurableSet_image</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">mpr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
